    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="729"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1751.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1911</hi>
                        </date>,</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 33.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to your note of the 3d instant,
                    stating that the armistice is being taken advantage of to send arms and
                    ammunition for insurgents into Mexican territory, I have the honor to inform you
                    that the Department is advised by the Department of Justice that this
                    information was communicated to the United States marshal for the western
                    district of Texas, by telegraph, on the 3d instant.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
